race.comment: Looks a wide-open contest. CHICAGO KING (2) finally shed the maiden tag at the Gold Coast last time out and will have taken a bunch of confidence from that breakthrough victory. Winning hoop Thornton sticks in the stirrups and should get the run of the race from the inside alley. Plenty to like about his prospects. Former Victorian HOME ZONE (14) wasn't too far away when having the first run for the new stable and should find this easier than what she faced down south. Can feature with natural improvement. BELLOVE (15) got the maiden out of the way here at the latest outing and Graham stays on top. In the mix. MANHATTAN'S (12) was a touch disappointing last start but the form prior was full of merit. Can bounce right back without surprising. BEST COFFEE (6) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be underestimated.
